🧠 Prompts Used – Luvelle Love Sync
This project was built using an AI-powered vibecoding approach on Base44. Instead of traditional coding, the application was designed through structured prompts defining logic, UI, and user experience.

💡 Core Idea Prompt
Create a relationship-focused web application where two users can privately express feelings. The system should only reveal results when both users' responses match. The experience must feel safe, minimal, and emotionally intelligent.

🔐 Privacy & Logic Prompt
Design a mutual syncing system where:

User A submits input privately
User B submits input privately
No user can see the other's response unless both match
If inputs do not match, keep results hidden
Avoid any exposure of one-sided feelings
🎨 UI/UX Design Prompt
Create a soft, aesthetic interface using a light maroon and beige color palette. The design should feel calm, warm, and minimal. Avoid clutter and focus on spacing, typography, and emotional comfort.

⚡ Interaction Flow Prompt
Build a smooth user flow:

User enters the app
Inputs their feeling
Waits for partner input
System checks for match
Displays result only if both match
🧠 Experience Enhancement Prompt
Design the experience to reduce anxiety and overthinking. Avoid negative signals, harsh feedback, or pressure. Keep the system neutral and emotionally safe.

🔄 Iteration Prompt
Refine the system to ensure:

Fast interaction
Clear flow
Mobile responsiveness
Clean transitions
🚀 Outcome
Using these prompts, the platform generated:

Frontend UI
Backend logic
Data workflows
Fully deployed application
This project demonstrates a vibecoding approach where ideas are translated directly into functional products.